\fs22
AIBox is an offline AI tutor stack for Latin American students. It bundles a local LLM, Wikipedia, the Kolibri learning platform, and a custom AI chat service, all running on this PC with no internet required at use time.\par
\par
This installer will:\par
\par
\b Phase A \b0 — copy the AIBox files into the install folder and (if needed) install Docker Desktop. Takes about 5 minutes.\par
\par
\b Phase B \b0 — download ~100 GB of models, Wikipedia, and the search index. Takes several hours on a typical connection. Resumable.\par
\par
\b Phase C \b0 — generate secrets, create your admin account, and verify the stack starts. Takes about 10 minutes.\par
\par
Have on hand: a fast internet connection, at least 150 GB free on C:, and an NVIDIA GPU. We cannot install on AMD or Apple Silicon.\par
